Je&s;&s;amine, Honey-&s;uckles and Ro&s;e-trees
form'd by intermixing their Boughs. The Princely
Ram told <HI>Miranda,</HI> &startq;That he had reign'd Sove|reign
there &s;everal Years, and had &s;ufficient cau&s;e
to be afflicted, but that he refrain'd from his
Tears, that he might not remind her of her Mi&s;|fortunes.&endq;
&startq;Your manner of Treatment, charm|ing
Sheep, <HI>&s;aid &s;he,</HI> is &s;omewhat &s;o generous, that
I cannot expre&s;s my Acknowledgment enough $
and I mu&s;t confe&s;s, that what I &s;ee &s;eems
&s;o extraordinary, I know not what to think of
it.&endq; No &s;ooner had &s;he pronouc'd the&s;e Words,
but there appear'd a Troop of beautiful Nymphs,
who pre&s;ented her with Fruit out of Amber Ba&s;|kets;
but when &s;he went nigh them, they in&s;en|&s;ibly
<PB N="31" REF="40">
mov'd from her; and at la&s;t reaching out her
$and to take hold of one of them, and feeling
$othing, &s;he &s;oon perceiv'd they were only Phan|toms.
&startq;Alas! <HI>&s;aid &s;he, weeping,</HI> where am I, and
what were the&s;e?&endq; At that in&s;tant the <HI>Royal
