and clapping my Hand upon my Sword, was going
to &s;acrifice her to the <HI>Manes</HI> of that dear Slave,
had &s;he not render'd me motionle&s;s by her Art. My
Efforts being vain, I fell on the Ground, and endea|vour'd
to kill my &s;elf, to deliver my &s;elf from that
wretched State I was reduc'd to; when &s;he, with
an ironical Smile, &s;aid to me, &startq;I will make you
feel my Power; you are at pre&s;ent a Lion, but
&s;hall e'er long be a Sheep.&endq; Whereupon touching
me with her Wand, I found my&s;elf metamorpho&s;ed,
&s;uch as you &s;ee me, but retain both my Speech, and
tho&s;e Senti$ents of Grief which I owe to my un|happy
State. &startq;Thou &s;halt be five Years a Sheep,
<HI>continued &s;he,</HI> and ab&s;olute Ma&s;ter of this &s;weet A|bode;
while I &s;eparated from thee, and never be|holding
thy agreeable Form, &s;hall think on no|thing
but the Hatred I bear thee.&endq; Hereupon &s;he
di&s;appear'd, and if any thing could have &s;often'd my
Misfortunes, or given any Allay to my Di&s;grace,
'twas her Ab&s;ence.</P>
<P>The Sheep &s;he &s;poke of, acknowledged me to be
their King, told me all their Misfortunes, how
they di&s;plea&s;ed the revengeful Fairy, how &s;he had
compo&s;ed a Flock of them, and that they all under|went
the &s;ame Puni&s;hment. But, <HI>added $e,</HI> when
their Time is expired, they re&s;ume their own
Forms, and leave the Flock; and for tho&s;e who are
<HI>Ragott$</HI>'s Ri$$ls or Enemies, whom &s;he has kill'd,
they abide here an Age before they return in$o
the World again: of which number the young
<PB N="34" REF="43">
Slave is, whom I told you of. I have &s;een her &s;eve|ral
Months together, but &s;he never &s;peaks to me;
and when I approach'd towards her, it grieved me,
when I knew it was only a Shadow: but having
ob&s;erved one of my Flock always by that Phantom,
I under&s;tood he was her Lover, whom <HI>Ragotte,</HI> jea|lous
